Ask HN: Are there places to have nuanced conversations online?
text:
As per the title, are there places where people still have nuanced conversations online? Especially conversations that span across multiple days.

Because even here on HN where conversations are, for the most part, fairly great you still have the issue of new content coming up daily and so the conversation has to move on the new topic.

I personally had luck using emails to interact with people but I was wondering if other people had different experiences.

Show HN: RxJS Insights – a toolset for RxJS visualization
text:
Hi HN! I'd like to present you the thing that I'm building - the RxJS Insights. It was primarily created as something that allows for debugging complex RxJS streams, but after showing it to a few people it turned out that it might be more helpful in learning RxJS since it can visualize the observables execution step by step.

The setup is somewhat similar to the Redux Devtools' one in a sense that it requires an application level component (the proper @rxjs-insights/* packages) to instrument the RxJS and to connect with the devtools.

I invite you to try it out in your app (the setup is rather easy) or on StackBlitz (all links are in the readme).

Thanks!
